This test tries to use comma delimited corbaloc with FT_Client_ORB.

To run automatically, execute "./run_test.sh"

To run the test manually:

- run 2 servers:

./server -ORBEndPoint iiop://:9220
./server -ORBEndPoint iiop://:9221

- run client:

echo "corbaloc:iiop:localhost:9220,iiop:localhost:9221/CorbaSimple" | \
        ./client -ORBSvcConf client.conf

expected behaviour:

- client invokes RPC on the first server(9220)
- server(9220) serves the request and shuts down
- client sleeps, then issues another request
- request is server by server(9221)

Test prepared by milan.cvetkovic@mpathix.com
